Task 1 a):

A. Explanation

In order to understand if bookmakers are good at deciding over 2.5 odds, I draw a scatter plot of implied “over” probability average in a bin versus the fraction of games finished over for the corresponding bin. And also I draw the line (x=y). I chose 5 bookmaker respectively : Pinnacle, Unibet, 10Bet, Tipico and Betsson. In order to fraction of the games finished over is meaningful, according to the cases I merge bins in such cases.

B. Comments of plots

  1. Pinnacle for initial odds:

For compute to meaningful statistic, I tried different probability intervals according to number of games in these bins and I determined cut point as 0.25. For a successful bookmaker these points should be on the line(x=y). Therefore when we consider the plot we can conclude that: Pinnacle is a successful bookmaker. Sure there are some outliers but they can be negligible. In general we can say that Pinnacle’s odds are trustable for over/under bet types for over odds.

  1. Pinnacle for final odds:

For compute to meaningful statistic, I tried different probability intervals according to number of games in these bins and I determined cut point as 0.25. For a successful bookmaker these points should be on the line(x=y which means predicted probabilities and emprical probabilities almost same). Therefore when we consider the plot we can conclude that: Pinnacle is a successful bookmaker. Sure there are some outliers but they can be negligible. When we compare this plot with Pinnacle’s initial odds plot, we can also observe that prediction of odds became much more trustable. Because these points are more look like on the line. In general we can say that Pinnacle’s odds are trustable for over/under bet types for over odds.

  1. Unibet for initial odds:

For compute to meaningful statistic, I tried different probability intervals according to number of games in these bins and I determined cut point as 0.25. Task 1 b):

A. Explanation

In order to perform this task, I used ggplot2. It allowed me draw plot seperately for each bin with help of facet_wrap at once. Bins can be seen at top of the plot. For task 1 and b part, I chose Pinnacle as a bookmaker. For compute the meaningful statistic, I chose bin 0.25. Because below this cut point, there were bins with little observations (i.e. 3 games). In addition, I used final odds for evaluate the success of the bookmaker. Due to I couldn’t add the label the plot, I should explain what the colors represent:

Blue: Implied over probability

Red: Emprical over probability

B.Comment

When I look the (0.25, 0.5] bin in 2011, 2014, 2017 and 2018 years, Pinnacle’s success of determining “over” probabilities is perfect. In rest of the years in given time period also Pinnacle’s success is good just in 2016 gap between emprical and implied probabilities is high. When I look the (0.5, 0.75] bin in 2012, 2013, 2014, 2017 and 2018 years, Pinnacle’s success of determining “over” probabilities is very good. In rest of the years in given time period, Pinnacle’s success of determining “over” probabilities is also pretty good.

3. APPENDIX

** Appendix: R codes for Plotting Figures**

3.1. Task 1 a):

3.1.1. Code for Figure 1:

require(data.table)

require(anytime)

matches=unique(matches)

matches[,match_date:=anydate(date)]

matches[,match_time:=anytime(date)]

matches=matches[order(home,-match_time)]

matches[,c(“match_date”,“date”):=NULL]

matches[,c(“HomeGoals”,“AwayGoals”):=tstrsplit(score,‘:’)]

matches[,Year:=year(match_time)]

matches[,Month:=month(match_time)]

matches[,Weekday:=wday(match_time)]

matches[,Hour:=hour(match_time)]

matches\(HomeGoals=as.numeric(matches\)HomeGoals)

matches[,AwayGoals:=as.numeric(AwayGoals)]

matches[,TotalGoals:=HomeGoals+AwayGoals]

matches[,IsOver:=0]

matches[TotalGoals>2,IsOver:=1]

matches[is.na(score)]

matches=matches[complete.cases(matches)]

odds_over_under=odd_details[betType==‘ou’ & totalhandicap==‘2.5’]

odds_over_under[,totalhandicap:=NULL]

odds_over_under=odds_over_under[order(matchId, oddtype,bookmaker,date)]

odds_over_under_initial=odds_over_under[,list(start_odd=odd[1]), by=list(matchId,oddtype,bookmaker)]

odds_over_under_final=odds_over_under[,list(final_odd=odd[.N]), by=list(matchId,oddtype,bookmaker)]

wide_odds_initial=dcast(odds_over_under_initial, matchId~oddtype+bookmaker, value.var=‘start_odd’)

wide_odds_final=dcast(odds_over_under_final, matchId~oddtype+bookmaker, value.var=‘final_odd’)

pinnacle_over_under=odds_over_under_initial[bookmaker==‘Pinnacle’]

pinnacle_wide=dcast(pinnacle_over_under, matchId~oddtype, value.var=‘start_odd’)

merged_matches=merge(matches,pinnacle_wide,by=‘matchId’)

merged_matches[,probOver:=1/over]

merged_matches[,probUnder:=1/under]

merged_matches[,totalProb:=probOver+probUnder]

merged_matches[,probOver:=probOver/totalProb]

merged_matches[,probUnder:=probUnder/totalProb]

merged_matches=merged_matches[complete.cases(merged_matches)]

merged_matches[,totalProb:=NULL]

cutpoints=seq(0,1,0.25)

merged_matches[,odd_cut_over:=cut(probOver,cutpoints)]

summary_table=merged_matches[,list(empirical_over=mean(IsOver), probabilistic_over=mean(probOver),.N), by=list(Year,odd_cut_over)]

summary_table=summary_table[order(Year)]

plot(summary_table[,list(empirical_over,probabilistic_over)],cex=4)

abline(0,1,col=‘red’)

pinnacle_1x2_initial=odds_1x2_initial[bookmaker==‘Pinnacle’]

pinnacle_wide_initial=dcast(pinnacle_1x2_initial, matchId~oddtype, value.var=‘start_odd’)

pinnacle_1x2_final=odds_1x2_final[bookmaker==‘Pinnacle’]

pinnacle_wide_final=dcast(pinnacle_1x2_final, matchId~oddtype, value.var=‘final_odd’)

merged_matches_initial=merge(matches,pinnacle_wide_initial,by=‘matchId’)

merged_matches_final=merge(matches,pinnacle_wide_final,by=‘matchId’)

merged_matches_initial[,probOdd1:=1/odd1]

merged_matches_initial[,probOdd2:=1/odd2]

merged_matches_initial[,probOddX:=1/oddX]

merged_matches_final[,probOdd1:=1/odd1]

merged_matches_final[,probOdd2:=1/odd2]

merged_matches_final[,probOddX:=1/oddX]

merged_matches_initial[,totalProb:=probOdd1+probOdd2+probOddX]

merged_matches_final[,totalProb:=probOdd1+probOdd2+probOddX]

merged_matches_initial[,probOdd1:=probOdd1/totalProb]

merged_matches_final[,probOdd1:=probOdd1/totalProb]

merged_matches_initial[,probOdd2:=probOdd2/totalProb]

merged_matches_final[,probOdd2:=probOdd2/totalProb]

merged_matches_initial[,probOddX:=probOddX/totalProb]

merged_matches_final[,probOddX:=probOddX/totalProb]

merged_matches_initial=merged_matches_initial[complete.cases(merged_matches_initial)]

merged_matches_initial[,totalProb:=NULL]

merged_matches_final=merged_matches_final[complete.cases(merged_matches_final)]

merged_matches_final[,totalProb:=NULL]

cutpoints=seq(0,1,0.25)

merged_matches_initial[,odd_cut_odd1:=cut(probOdd1,cutpoints)]

merged_matches_initial[,odd_cut_odd2:=cut(probOdd2,cutpoints)]

merged_matches_initial[,odd_cut_oddX:=cut(probOddX,cutpoints)]

merged_matches_final[,odd_cut_odd1:=cut(probOdd1,cutpoints)]

merged_matches_final[,odd_cut_odd2:=cut(probOdd2,cutpoints)]

merged_matches_final[,odd_cut_oddX:=cut(probOddX,cutpoints)]

summary_table_initial=merged_matches_initial[,list(empirical_odd1=mean(IsOdd1),probabilistic_odd1=mean(probOdd1),empirical_odd2=mean(IsOdd2),probabilistic_odd2=mean(probOdd2),empirical_oddX=mean(IsOddX),probabilistic_oddX=mean(probOddX),.N),by=list(Year,odd_cut_odd1,odd_cut_odd2,odd_cut_oddX)]

summary_table_final=merged_matches_final[,list(empirical_odd1=mean(IsOdd1),probabilistic_odd1=mean(probOdd1),empirical_odd2=mean(IsOdd2),probabilistic_odd2=mean(probOdd2),empirical_oddX=mean(IsOddX),probabilistic_oddX=mean(probOddX),.N),by=list(Year,odd_cut_odd1,odd_cut_odd2,odd_cut_oddX)]

summary_table_initial=summary_table_initial[order(Year)]

summary_table_final=summary_table_final[order(Year)]

ggplot(data=summary_table_initial,aes((x = Year))) + geom_line(aes(y = probabilistic_odd1), color = “blue”) + geom_line( aes(y = empirical_odd1), color = “red” ) + geom_line(aes(y = probabilistic_odd2), color = “purple”) + geom_line( aes(y = empirical_odd2), color = “pink” ) + geom_line(aes(y = probabilistic_oddX), color = “black”) + geom_line( aes(y = empirical_oddX), color = “yellow” ) + facet_grid(odd_cut_odd2 ~ odd_cut_oddX ~ odd_cut_odd1) + xlab(‘Year’) +ylab(‘Probability’)

ggplot(data=summary_table_final,aes((x = Year))) + geom_line(aes(y = probabilistic_odd1), color = “blue”) + geom_line( aes(y = empirical_odd1), color = “red” ) + geom_line(aes(y = probabilistic_odd2), color = “purple”) + geom_line( aes(y = empirical_odd2), color = “pink” ) + geom_line(aes(y = probabilistic_oddX), color = “black”) + geom_line( aes(y = empirical_oddX), color = “yellow” ) + facet_grid(odd_cut_odd2 ~ odd_cut_oddX ~ odd_cut_odd1) + xlab(‘Year’) +ylab(‘Probability’)
